TELECOM ITALIA MASTERS
May 8, 2003
Ivan Ljubicic
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT
 
 
  
 
  
  
   
 
Q. Do you sort of feel like you're home when you're here? 
 
 IVAN LJUBICIC: Well, I am playing good in Italy but I don't know if it's -- I don't know why, really. I mean, it's different feeling than playing in Germany, but it's not like home. But still I have a lot of -- my three families of -- well, three brothers of my father, with all the family, they are living here in Rome. So always a lot of people cheering for me here in Rome.  
 
Q. A foster home? 
 
 IVAN LJUBICIC: Yeah (smiling).  
 
